personalInfo.education: Northwestern University (2011, Political Science and History)

tourBios.exmtStatus: Fully Exempt: # Nearest 50 - 21st Web.com Tour qualifier at 2012 PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.curYearHigh: Shot rounds of 67-64-66-65 at Crans-sur-Sierre GC to finish regulation tied with Graeme Strom at the Omega European Masters. In the sudden-death playoff, made a par on the first extra hole to Storm's bogey to secure his first European Tour title. Improved from No. 369 in the OWGR at the beginning of the week to No. 154.
tourBios.carHigh: 2012: Has never made a start in either a PGA TOUR event or a Web.com Tour event prior to the beginning of the 2013 season. Won the Asian Tour Qualifying School in January and went on to finish seventh on the Tour's Order of Merit. Made the cut in seven of 12 starts and had five top-10 finishes. Won the Handa Faldo Cambodian Classic when he chipped in to defeat Elmer Salvador in a playoff. Started the final round tied for eighth and was seven strokes off the pace but rallied with a closing 65...Followed in his next start with a T2 at the Handa Singapore Open, falling one shot back of winner Scott Hend of Australia...Was T3 in his next start, at the Maybank Malaysian Open, a tournament won by Louis Oosthuizen...Qualified for the CIMB Classic in Malaysia, where he T44...The following week, played in his first World Golf Championships events, the HSBC Champions in China. Shot a third-round 69 on his way to a T72 finish.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Amateur: Played college golf at Northwestern, where he won twice, including the 2010 Big Ten Championship. Was an All-American in 2011...Was a three-time league champion at La Canada High School in California.
tourBios.personal: Caddied throughout college...Favorite golf memory was making a hole-in-one on No. 7 at Pebble Beach...If he were not a golfer, would want to work in the entertainment industry...Is a fan of the Los Angeles Lakers, Los Angeles Kings and Oakland Raiders...Not many people know he is only half-Asian...Twitter account is @David_Lipsky.
